<body id="bg">
    <div class="header-img"><img src="~/images/main-slider/header.png" alt="Header Image" /></div>
    <div class="blog-main-container">
        <div class="latest-bikes-details-content">
            <h3 class="subheading"> Exploring the Maruti Suzuki S-Presso — A Bold City Car with SUV Attitude</h3>
            <p>The Maruti Suzuki S-Presso is a unique offering in the entry-level hatchback segment, blending SUV-inspired styling with Maruti’s hallmark reliability and efficiency. Designed for the young and adventurous, the S-Presso brings personality, practicality, and affordability into one compact package.</p>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/may/marutispresso/banner.png" alt="banner" title="banner" /></div>
            </div>
            <h3 class="subheading"> Design and Presence</h3>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/may/marutispresso/highlight4.webp" alt="interior" title="interior" /></div>
            </div>
            <p>With its upright stance, bold front grille, and squared-off wheel arches, the S-Presso channels a mini-SUV vibe. The tall-boy design not only improves visibility but also provides an easy ingress/egress experience. It’s available in eye-catching colors like Solid Fire Red, Sizzle Orange, and White, helping it stand out in city traffic.</p>
            <h3 class="subheading">Performance and Fuel Economy</h3>
			<div class="row m-b20">				
                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/may/marutispresso/engine.webp" alt="engine" title="engine" /></div>
            </div>
            <p>Powered by the peppy <span class="font-weight-600">1.0L K10C petrol engine,</span> the S-Presso delivers <span class="font-weight-600">67PS</span> and <span class="font-weight-600">89Nm.</span> Whether you choose the manual or Auto Gear Shift (AGS) variant, you'll enjoy smooth city driving and exceptional fuel efficiency — up to <span class="font-weight-600">25.30 km/l</span> for AGS variants.</p>
            <h3 class="subheading">Interior and Features</h3>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/may/marutispresso/Interior2.webp" alt="Interior" title="Interior" /></div>
                <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/may/marutispresso/highlight3.webp" alt="highlight" title="highlight" /></div>
            </div>
            <p>Inside, the S-Presso sports a youthful dashboard with a centrally-mounted digital speedometer and infotainment cluster. Noteworthy features include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>SmartPlay Studio infotainment system (in higher variants)</li>
                <li>Front power windows</li>
                <li>Digital instrument display</li>
                <li>270L boot space</li>
            </ul>
            <h3 class="subheading">Safety</h3>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/may/marutispresso/exterior1.webp" alt="exterior" title="exterior" /></div>
            </div>
            <p>Standard safety features across variants include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Dual airbags</li>
                <li>ABS with EBD</li>
                <li>Reverse parking sensors</li>
                <li>Seatbelt reminders</li>
                <li>Speed alert system</li>
            </ul>
            <p> For <a class="for-link" asp-controller="ValueForMoney" asp-action="MarutiSuzukiSPresso_1">Maruti Suzuki S Presso - Value for Money Variant</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
